description.plain:
“I’m not Pretty” is JESSIA’s fifteenth single ever since the start of her career with “Eclipse” back in 2018. This song is about how people have judged her because of her weight and how people in society are hypocrites by saying things like “You’re perfect just the way you are.” “I’m not Pretty” also shows how JESSIA compares herself to the “standard” girl. The song was co-written and produced by Elijah Woods.

@dalmo

annotations:
’Cause I got a belly and I got a bum
 But I can’t be jelly of all the other ones
This lyric means that she feels like she’s fat and she knows that she shouldn’t be jealous of everyone else who doesn’t look fat

Every other song says I’m beautiful
 But what if I don’t feel like I’m beautiful?

2016’s “Scars to Your Beautiful” pushed the trope of songs building up people’s appearances, more specifically that of women. 2019 renewed the surge in body-positivity throughout music, with new-comers like Lizzo having positive anthems be the hallmark of their careers. Jessia, though, doesn’t feel affected by the songs' messages urging her to love herself and her appearance, instead falling for the lies of what an “average” woman should look like.
Maybe I’m not pretty, maybe I’m just fun

In an interview for Kiss 92.5, JESSIA opened up about the real-life experience that inspired the line:

So, it’s funny that it blew up on TikTok because it was inspired by a TikTok sound. I was hearing this sound that had gone viral that said, ‘I have never seen two pretty best friends,’ and it kinda just hit me for a sec, and I went, ‘Wait, all of my friends are, like, absolutely gorgeous, so maybe I’m not the pretty one, maybe I’m just the fun one of the group.’

description.plain:
Widely regarded among fans as one of JESSIA’s best songs, “Next Time” narrates her memories with an ex that now that he is out of her life, puts her on an immense feeling of sadness and nostalgia while she remembers their moments together.

She also understands, that although they have had such beautiful moments together, maybe they weren’t destinated to be toghether.

I’m not your type
Three years gone by, did I forget to mention
Almost your wife
You run and hide if it’s not fuckin' perfect

The title of the tracks serves as a warning of the “next time” he has a relationship with someone. Warning him that “if [he] needs advice” he should “just lie.”

description.plain:
“But I Don’T” is the last track and fourth single of JESSIA’s debut extended play, How Are You?. Different snippets of the song were shared through JESSIA’s her socials.
The song talks about being proposed to be in a relationship and, even though you considered the proposal, you tell them that “if I really wanted to I would, but I actually don’t.” It was finally released with the rest of the mini-album on October 15, 2021.
Days later, the music video of the song was released.

“Be Here Now” is the fifth track of JESSIA’s debut extended play, How Are You?. The original version of the song was first shared through an Instagram Live on July 18, 2020. It talks about being present during different situations of life like “hanging out with friends”, “falling in love,” and “following your dreams”.
The song was finally released with the rest of the mini-album on October 15, 2021.
